==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propel
<hw>Pro*pel"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Propelled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Propelling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>propellere</ets>, <ets>propulsum</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> forward +
<ets>pellere</ets> to drive. See <er>Pulse</er> a beating.]</ety>
<def>To drive forward; to urge or press onward by force; to move, or
cause to move; <as>as, the wind or steam <ex>propels</ex> ships; balls
are <ex>propelled</ex> by gunpowder.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propeller</ent>⟦br⟧
